name: Scrambled Eggs
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together eggs and milk. Melt butter in a non-stick pan over medium heat. Pour in egg mixture and cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Chicken Caesar Salad
instructions: Season chicken with salt and pepper. Grill or pan-fry until cooked through. Cut into bite-sized pieces. Wash and chop lettuce. In a large bowl, toss together lettuce, chicken, dressing, Parmesan cheese, and croutons.

name: Grilled Cheese Sandwich
instructions: Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Butter one side of each bread slice. Place one slice, butter-side down, in the pan. Top with cheese slices. Place the other slice of bread, butter-side up, on top. Cook until bread is toasted and cheese is melted, flipping once.

name: Baked Salmon
instructions: Preheat oven to 375Â°F. Place salmon fillet in a baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over the top. Drizzle with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until salmon is cooked through.

name: Blueberry Pancakes
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. In another bowl, whisk together milk, egg, and melted butter. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Gently fold in blueberries. Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Pour batter onto the pan, using about 1/4 cup per pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown.

name: Beef Stir-Fry
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together cornstarch, soy sauce, and oyster sauce. Heat vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over high heat. Add beef and cook until browned. Remove from pan. Add bell peppers, onion, snow peas, and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender. Add beef back to pan, along with sauce mixture. Stir until sauce thickens and everything is heated through.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: Arrange tomato slices and mozzarella slices on a plate, alternating between the two. Top with basil leaves. In a small bowl, whisk together balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Drizzle over the salad. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Classic Cheeseburger
instructions: 1. Preheat grill to high heat. 2. Form ground beef into four patties. 3. Grill patties for 3-4 minutes per side. 4. Add a slice of cheese to each patty during the last minute of cooking. 5. Toast buns on grill. 6. Spread mayonnaise on bottom buns and ketchup on top buns. 7. Place patties on bottom buns and cover with top buns. Serve hot.

name: Pesto Pasta
instruction: 1. Cook pasta according to package instructions. 2. Reserve 1/4 cup of pasta water. 3. In a small pan, toast pine nuts until lightly browned. 4. In a large bowl, mix together cooked pasta, pesto, parmesan cheese, garlic, and pine nuts. 5. Add reserved pasta water as needed to create a creamy sauce. 6. Serve hot.

name: Blueberry Pancakes
instruction: 1. In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. 2. In a separate bowl, whisk together buttermilk, egg, and melted butter. 3. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until just combined. 4. Gently fold in blueberries. 5. Heat a nonstick skillet or griddle over medium heat. 6. Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto skillet for each pancake. 7. Cook for 2-3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. 8. Serve hot with butter and syrup.

name: Fluffy Pancakes
instructions: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients. 2. In a separate bowl, whisk together the wet ingredients. 3. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. 4. Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat. 5. Spoon about 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake. 6. Cook until the edges are set and bubbles form on the surface. 7. Flip and cook until the other side is golden brown. 8. Serve hot with maple syrup and butter.

name: Classic French Toast
instructions: 1. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, vanilla extract, and cinnamon. 2. Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat. 3. Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, making sure to coat both sides. 4. Melt a small amount of butter in the skillet. 5. Add the bread slices and cook until golden brown on both sides. 6. Serve hot with maple syrup.

name: Classic Macaroni and Cheese
instructions: 1. Cook the macaroni according to package instructions. 2. In a separate saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. 3. Add the flour and whisk until smooth. 4. Gradually add the milk, whisking constantly, until the mixture is smooth. 5. Add the cheese, salt, and pepper and stir until the cheese is melted and the sauce is smooth. 6. Drain the macaroni and stir it into the cheese sauce. 7. Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and sprinkle with breadcrumbs. 8. Bake at 350Â°F for 20-25 minutes, until the top is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly.

name: Blueberry Pancakes
instructions: 1. Mix dry ingredients. 2. Add milk and mix. 3. Fold in blueberries. 4. Cook on a griddle. 5. Serve with syrup.

name: Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken
instructions: 1. Mix spinach and feta. 2. Cut a pocket in each chicken breast. 3. Stuff spinach and feta into pockets. 4. Season with garlic and olive oil. 5. Bake in the oven.

name: Avocado Toast
instructions: 1. Toast bread. 2. Mash avocado with lemon juice and salt. 3. Spread avocado on toast. 4. Sprinkle red pepper flakes. 5. Serve.

name: Baked Salmon
instructions: 1. Preheat oven. 2. Season salmon with lemon, butter, garlic, and dill. 3. Bake in the oven. 4. Serve with lemon wedges.

name: Egg Fried Rice
instructions: 1. Cook rice. 2. Scramble eggs. 3. Fry peas and carrots. 4. Mix rice, eggs, peas, and carrots. 5. Add soy sauce. 6. Fry for a few minutes. 7. Serve.

name: Greek Yogurt Parfait
instructions: 1. Layer Greek yogurt, granola, and berries in a glass. 2. Drizzle with honey. 3. Sprinkle with cinnamon. 4. Serve.

name: Vegetable Stir Fry
instructions: 1. Cut vegetables and tofu into bite-sized pieces. 2. Fry garlic and ginger in a wok. 3. Add vegetables and tofu. 4. Stir-fry for a few minutes. 5. Add soy sauce. 6. Serve over rice.

name: Quinoa Salad
instructions: 1. Cook quinoa. 2. Cut cherry tomatoes and cucumber. 3. Mix quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and feta cheese. 4. Drizzle with olive oil. 5. Serve.

name: Omelette
instructions: 1. Whisk eggs in a bowl. 2. Add cheese, ham, mushrooms, and spinach. 3. Fry in a pan. 4. Serve.

name: Baked Potato
instructions: 1. Preheat oven. 2. Poke potatoes with a fork. 3. Rub with butter. 4. Bake in the oven. 5. Top with sour cream, cheddar cheese, and bacon bits. 6. Serve.

name: Avocado Toast
instructions: 1. Toast bread. 2. Mash avocado with lemon juice, salt, and pepper. 3. Spread on toast. 4. Serve.

name: Pesto Pasta
instructions: 1. Cook pasta. 2. Fry garlic and cherry tomatoes in a pan. 3. Add cooked pasta and basil pesto. 4. Stir. 5. Top with parmesan cheese. 6. Serve.

name: Roasted Chicken
instructions: 1. Preheat oven. 2. Rub chicken with olive oil, lemon juice, rosemary, and garlic. 3. Roast in the oven. 4. Serve.

name: French Toast
instructions: 1. Whisk eggs, milk, cinnamon, and vanilla extract in a bowl. 2. Dip bread in the mixture. 3. Fry in a pan. 4. Serve with syrup and butter.

name: Baked Salmon
instructions: 1. Preheat oven. 2. Rub salmon with olive oil, lemon juice, dill, and garlic. 3. Bake in the oven. 4. Serve.

name: Omelette
instructions: 1. Whisk eggs and salt in a bowl. 2. Fry mushrooms and spinach in a pan. 3. Pour eggs over vegetables. 4. Sprinkle cheese on top. 5. Cook until set. 6. Fold in half. 7. Serve.

name: Grilled Cheese Sandwich
instructions: 1. Butter bread. 2. Add cheese between bread slices. 3. Sprinkle garlic powder and paprika. 4. Grill in a pan until cheese is melted. 5. Serve.

name: Stir Fry Vegetables
instructions: 1. Cut vegetables into small pieces. 2. Fry garlic and onion in a pan. 3. Add vegetables. 4. Stir fry until cooked. 5. Add soy sauce. 6. Serve.

name: Chicken Caesar Salad
instructions: 1. Cook chicken. 2. Cut lettuce into bite-sized pieces. 3. Add parmesan cheese, croutons, and cooked chicken. 4. Toss with caesar dressing. 5. Serve.

name: Pesto Chicken Pasta
instructions: 1. Cook pasta. 2. Cook chicken. 3. Fry cherry tomatoes in a pan. 4. Add cooked pasta, chicken, and basil pesto. 5. Stir. 6. Top with parmesan cheese. 7. Serve.

name: Avocado Toast
instructions: 1. Toast bread. 2. Mash avocado with salt, pepper, and lemon juice. 3. Spread avocado on toast. 4. Serve.

name: Vegetable Curry
instructions: 1. Cut vegetables into small pieces. 2. Fry garlic and onion in a pan. 3. Add vegetables. 4. Add curry powder. 5. Cook until vegetables are soft. 6. Serve.

name: Tuna Salad
instructions: 1. Drain canned tuna. 2. Cut lettuce and celery into small pieces. 3. Mix tuna, lettuce, and celery in a bowl. 4. Add mayonnaise and lemon juice. 5. Toss. 6. Serve.

name: Beef Tacos
instructions: 1. Cook beef. 2. Cut lettuce and tomato into small pieces. 3. Heat taco shells in the oven. 4. Add cooked beef, lettuce, and tomato to taco shells. 5. Top with sour cream. 6. Serve.

name: Frittata
instructions: 1. Whisk eggs, milk, and salt in a bowl. 2. Add spinach and cheese. 3. Pour mixture into a pan. 4. Cook until set. 5. Serve.

name: Spaghetti Bolognese
instructions: 1. Cook spaghetti. 2. Fry garlic and onion in a pan. 3. Add ground beef. 4. Cook until brown. 5. Add tomato sauce. 6. Simmer for 10 minutes. 7. Serve.

name: Egg Salad Sandwich
instructions: 1. Chop boiled eggs. 2. Mix eggs, mayonnaise, and mustard in a bowl. 3. Add salt and pepper to taste. 4. Assemble sandwich with egg mixture and lettuce. 5. Serve.

name: Chicken Alfredo
instructions: 1. Cook fettuccine pasta. 2. Cut chicken breast into small pieces. 3. Fry chicken in a pan. 4. Add heavy cream and butter. 5. Add Parmesan cheese. 6. Simmer until sauce thickens. 7. Serve.

name: Blueberry Pancakes
instructions: 1. Mix pancake mix, milk, eggs, and melted butter in a bowl. 2. Add blueberries to the batter. 3. Pour batter onto a hot griddle. 4. Cook until bubbles form. 5. Flip and cook until golden brown. 6. Serve.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: 1. Slice tomatoes and mozzarella cheese. 2. Arrange tomatoes and mozzarella cheese on a plate. 3. Add basil leaves. 4. Drizzle olive oil and balsamic vinegar. 5. Serve.

name: Baked Ziti
instructions: 1. Cook ziti pasta. 2. Brown ground beef in a pan. 3. Mix cooked pasta, ground beef, marinara sauce, and ricotta cheese in a baking dish. 4. Top with mozzarella cheese. 5. Bake in oven for 25 minutes. 6. Serve.

name: Pesto Chicken
instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 400Â°F. 2. Season chicken breast with salt and pepper. 3. Spread pesto sauce over chicken. 4. Add sliced tomatoes on top. 5. Top with mozzarella cheese. 6. Drizzle olive oil. 7. Bake in oven for 20-25 minutes. 8. Serve.

name: Huevos Rancheros
instructions: 1. Heat tortillas in a pan. 2. Spread refried beans on top of tortillas. 3. Add salsa. 4. Fry eggs. 5. Place eggs on top of tortillas. 6. Top with cheddar cheese. 7. Serve.

name: Beef Tacos
instructions: 1. Brown ground beef in a pan. 2. Add taco seasoning. 3. Heat taco shells in the oven. 4. Assemble tacos with ground beef, lettuce, and tomatoes. 5. Serve.

name: Cobb Salad
instructions: 1. Cook chicken breast and bacon. 2. Chop lettuce. 3. Add sliced chicken breast, bacon, hard boiled eggs, and sliced avocado. 4. Serve with dressing of your choice.

name: Vegetarian Burrito Bowl
instructions: 1. Cook brown rice. 2. Heat black beans and corn in a pan. 3. Dice tomatoes and avocado. 4. Assemble burrito bowl with rice, black beans, corn, tomatoes, and avocado. 5. Serve.

name: Beef Stroganoff
instructions: 1. Slice beef sirloin into thin strips. 2. SautÃ© beef and onion in a pan until beef is browned. 3. Add mushrooms and beef broth to pan. 4. Simmer until mushrooms are cooked. 5. Remove pan from heat and stir in sour cream. 6. Serve over cooked egg noodles.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: 1. Slice tomatoes and mozzarella cheese. 2. Arrange tomatoes and mozzarella cheese on a plate. 3. Top with basil leaves. 4. Drizzle balsamic vinegar and olive oil over salad. 5. Serve.

name: Honey Mustard Chicken
instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375Â°F. 2. Mix honey, dijon mustard, minced garlic, and chopped thyme in a bowl. 3. Spread mixture over chicken thighs. 4. Bake chicken in oven for 35-40 minutes. 5. Serve.

name: Pesto Pasta Salad
instructions: 1. Cook rotini pasta. 2. Halve cherry tomatoes. 3. Mix cooked pasta with cherry tomatoes, basil pesto, and grated parmesan cheese. 4. Toast pine nuts in a pan. 5. Add pine nuts to pasta salad. 6. Serve.

name: Sweet and Sour Pork
instructions: 1. Cut pork loin into bite-sized pieces. 2. SautÃ© pork, bell pepper, and onion in a pan until pork is browned. 3. Add pineapple chunks, sliced carrots, and sweet and sour sauce to the pan. 4. Simmer until pork is cooked and vegetables are tender. 5. Serve over rice.

name: Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken
instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375Â°F. 2. Mix chopped spinach, crumbled feta cheese, garlic powder, and paprika in a bowl. 3. Cut a pocket in each chicken breast. 4. Stuff each chicken breast with spinach and feta mixture. 5. Bake chicken in oven for 35-40 minutes. 6. Serve.

name: Avocado Toast
instructions: 1. Toast bread. 2. Cut open avocado and remove pit. 3. Mash avocado with a fork. 4. Add lemon juice and salt to mashed avocado. 5. Spread avocado mixture on toast. 6. Sprinkle with red pepper flakes. 7. Serve.

name: Sausage and Egg Breakfast Burrito
instructions: 1. Cook sausage links. 2. Scramble eggs in a pan. 3. Heat tortillas in a separate pan. 4. Assemble burrito with scrambled eggs, sliced sausage, shredded cheddar cheese, and salsa. 5. Roll up burrito. 6. Serve.

name: Pesto Pasta with Roasted Tomatoes
instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 400Â°F. 2. Cut cherry tomatoes in half and place on a baking sheet. 3. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic. 4. Roast tomatoes in oven for 15-20 minutes. 5. Cook pasta according to package instructions. 6. Drain pasta and toss with basil pesto. 7. Serve pasta with roasted tomatoes and grated parmesan cheese.

name: Greek Salad
instructions: 1. Wash and chop romaine lettuce. 2. Dice cucumbers and tomatoes. 3. Mix lettuce, cucumbers, tomatoes, and kalamata olives in a bowl. 4. Crumble feta cheese over salad. 5. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice. 6. Serve.

name: Chicken and Broccoli Alfredo
instructions: 1. Cook fettuccine pasta according to package instructions. 2. Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces and cook in a pan until browned. 3. Blanch broccoli in boiling water for 2-3 minutes. 4. In a separate pan, heat heavy cream and grated parmesan cheese until cheese is melted. 5. Add cooked pasta, chicken, and broccoli to the pan with the Alfredo sauce. 6. Toss until everything is coated in the sauce. 7. Serve.

name: Shrimp Tacos
instructions: 1. Heat taco shells in oven according to package instructions. 2. Cook shrimp in a pan until pink. 3. Assemble tacos with lettuce, chopped tomatoes, cooked shrimp, and a dollop of sour cream. 4. Serve.

name: Banana Pancakes
instructions: 1. In a large bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar. 2. In a separate bowl, beat together milk and eggs. 3. Mash bananas and add them to the milk mixture. 4. Add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. 5. Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. 6. Pour batter onto the pan, using 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake. 7. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until both sides are golden brown. 8. Serve with butter and syrup.

name: Veggie Stir-Fry
instructions: 1. Cut broccoli into small florets. 2. Peel and slice carrots. 3. Slice mushrooms. 4. Cut red bell pepper into thin strips. 5. Cut onion into thin slices. 6. Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat. 7. Add a tablespoon of oil and swirl to coat. 8. Add vegetables to the wok and stir-fry for 3-4 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp. 9. Serve over rice or noodles.

name: Tomato Soup
instructions: 1. Cut tomatoes into quarters. 2. Peel and chop onion. 3. Peel and chop garlic. 4. In a large pot, sautÃ© onion and garlic in oil until soft. 5. Add tomatoes and vegetable broth. 6. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for 20-30 minutes. 7. Use an immersion blender to puree soup until smooth. 8. Stir in heavy cream. 9. Serve with crusty bread.

name: Beef Stroganoff
instructions: 1. Slice beef into thin strips. 2. Slice onion. 3. Slice mushrooms. 4. In a large skillet, cook beef over medium-high heat until browned. 5. Remove beef from skillet and set aside. 6. In the same skillet, sautÃ© onion and mushrooms until tender. 7. Add beef broth to the skillet and bring to a boil. 8. Reduce heat and simmer for 10-15 minutes. 9. Stir in sour cream until heated through. 10. Serve over egg noodles or rice.

name: Blueberry Muffins
instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375Â°F. 2. In a large bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar. 3. In a separate bowl, beat together milk, eggs, and melted butter. 4. Add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. 5. Fold in blueberries. 6. Grease a muffin tin or line with paper liners. 7. Fill muffin cups with batter, using 1/4 cup of batter for each muffin. 8. Bake for 20-25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. 9. Let cool for 5 minutes before removing from muffin tin. 10. Serve warm or at room temperature.

name: Spinach Salad
instructions: 1. Wash spinach leaves and pat dry. 2. Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble. 3. Peel and chop hard-boiled eggs. 4. Thinly slice red onion. 5. Toss spinach leaves with bacon, eggs, and red onion. 6. Top with croutons. 7. Serve with your favorite salad dressing.
